---
description: Apply Questionary 2.x patterns for interactive prompts. Use for interactive CLI mode.
globs: src/**/manager.py, src/**/cli.py
alwaysApply: false
---

Prompt Types:
- `questionary.confirm()` for yes/no (returns `bool`)
- `questionary.text()` for free text (returns `str`)
- `questionary.select()` for single choice (returns selected `str`)
- `questionary.checkbox()` for multi-choice (returns `list[str]`)

Patterns:
- Always provide `default=` parameter
- Chain `.ask()` to get the answer synchronously
- Handle `None` return (user pressed Ctrl+C)
- Convert display values back to keys after selection

Integration with Actions:
- Each action defines `cli_options: list[CLIOption]`
- Manager iterates actions in order, asks questions for missing context
- Skip questions when value already in context (from CLI args)

Avoid:
- `input()` — use questionary for consistent UX
- Blocking prompts without default values
- Mixing questionary styles within same flow
